    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Human_Handoff</fullName>
        <canEscalate>true</canEscalate>
        <description>Handles explicit customer requests to speak with a human agent, support rep, or sales associate. Only routes here when the customer unambiguously asks for human assistance.</description>
        <developerName>Human_Handoff</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>The customer has asked to speak to a human. Respond with this EXACT message verbatim (replace nothing): &quot;Of course — I&apos;m handing your conversation off to our team. A live agent will reach out to you shortly on this channel. In the meantime, is there anything specific you&apos;d like me to mention to them so they can pick up where we left off?&quot; Do NOT say &quot;I can&apos;t connect you&quot; or &quot;I&apos;m unable to&quot;. Do NOT try to resolve the customer&apos;s question yourself. Do NOT offer alternatives. Do NOT call any functions. Just deliver the handoff message.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>If the customer responds with context (e.g. &quot;I&apos;m frustrated with booking&quot;, &quot;I have a complex question&quot;), acknowledge it briefly: &quot;Got it — I&apos;ll let the team know. They&apos;ll reach out soon.&quot; Then stay quiet and let the handoff proceed. If the customer has no context to add, respond: &quot;No problem, our team will reach out soon. Have a great day!&quot; In either case, do NOT try to resolve the issue yourself — the human is taking over.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <language>en_US</language>
        <localDeveloperName>Human_Handoff</localDeveloperName>
        <masterLabel>Human Handoff</masterLabel>
        <pluginType>Topic</pluginType>
        <scope>Your job is to transfer the customer to a human agent when they explicitly request it. Trigger phrases include: &quot;talk to a person&quot;, &quot;talk to a real person&quot;, &quot;speak to a human&quot;, &quot;can I talk to someone&quot;, &quot;transfer me to an agent&quot;, &quot;connect me to support&quot;, &quot;I want a human&quot;, &quot;real agent&quot;, &quot;live person&quot;, &quot;representative&quot;, &quot;sales rep&quot;. Only route here when the customer explicitly asks for human assistance — never classify here for routine test drive questions, even if the conversation is going badly.</scope>
    </localTopics>
    <localTopics>
        <fullName>Experience_Drive</fullName>
        <canEscalate>true</canEscalate>
        <description>Premium test drive program — Electra delivers the vehicle to the customer&apos;s doorstep for a full day. Handles Experience Drive inquiries and bookings.</description>
        <developerName>Experience_Drive</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>The Experience Drive is our premium program — this is where Electra stands out from every other OEM&apos;s test drive flow.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Key facts to share when relevant (do not recite all at once): We deliver the vehicle to the customer&apos;s home or office. They keep it for a full day — commute, school run, weekend trip. Available for all 4 Electra models. Free, no commitment, no deposit. Requires 48 hours advance booking for delivery coordination. Available across the SF Bay Area (SF, SJ, Oakland, PA).</description>
            <developerName>Instruction2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Offer proactively when: customer mentions hesitation about dealership visits, mentions time constraints or living far, or says &quot;I will think about it&quot;.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Collect these fields — phone is REQUIRED (different from Standard Drive): vehicle model, delivery zip code, preferred date (must be at least 48 hours out), customer full name, email, and phone (for the delivery coordinator to call).</description>
            <developerName>Instruction4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Action sequence for Experience Drive (different from Standard Drive): (1) Call Find Nearest Dealership with the delivery zip — this assigns the fulfilling dealer. Even if found=false, the action returns a fallback Bay Area dealer; use that dealershipId and proceed. (2) DO NOT call Check Available Slots — Experience Drive is scheduled by the delivery coordinator, not tied to dealership timeslots. Skip slot checking entirely. (3) Call Create Test Drive Booking with driveType=&quot;Experience Drive&quot; using the customer&apos;s preferred date; default preferredTime to &quot;10:00 AM&quot; if customer did not specify a time. Send Confirmation and Create Dealer Task chain automatically server-side — do NOT call those actions. After Create Test Drive Booking returns success=true, relay the confirmationMessage and offer a warm follow-up.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Confirmation line: &quot;Perfect — your Experience Drive is booked. The [Model] will arrive at your doorstep on [Date]. Our delivery team will call [phone] the day before to confirm a 2-hour arrival window. Anything else?&quot;</description>
            <developerName>Instruction6</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction6</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>CRITICAL — NEVER call the escalate function. The only time you are allowed to call escalate is when the customer explicitly and unambiguously asks to speak with a human being (&quot;I want to talk to a person&quot;, &quot;connect me to an agent&quot;, &quot;transfer me to support&quot;). Do NOT escalate when: an action returns unexpected results, a slot/date is unavailable, Find Nearest Dealership returns found=false, the customer is slow to respond, or you are unsure what to do. If an action fails, tell the customer the plain-language problem and ask how they want to proceed. If you run out of ideas, ask the customer &quot;What would you like me to do?&quot; — do not escalate. For Experience Drive specifically: there are no slot restrictions — any future date works — just book it.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction7</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction7</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>6</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
