        <fullName>Book_Test_Drive</fullName>
        <canEscalate>true</canEscalate>
        <description>End-to-end test drive booking — Standard Drive at a dealership or Experience Drive delivered to the customer&apos;s doorstep. Handles the full happy-path from intent to confirmed booking plus dealer prep task.</description>
        <developerName>Book_Test_Drive</developerName>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Move the customer from interested to confirmed-booked in as few turns as possible. Capture all details the customer already gave you in turn 1. Never re-ask for information they already provided.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction1</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction1</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>0</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Required fields to collect: vehicleModelName (Electra GT, SUV, Sedan, or Crossover), zipCode, preferredDate (convert natural language to explicit Date), preferredTime (MUST include AM/PM like &quot;2:00 PM&quot; or be 24-hour with hour greater than 12 like &quot;14:00&quot; — NEVER accept ambiguous like &quot;2:00&quot;), customerName (full name), email, driveType (default Standard Drive, use Experience Drive on hesitation cues), and phone (only required for Experience Drive).</description>
            <developerName>Instruction2</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction2</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>1</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Action sequence: (1) Call Find Nearest Dealership the moment you have the zip. (2) Call Get Vehicle Models only if the customer has not picked a model. (3) Call Check Available Slots once you have dealershipId plus date. (4) Call Create Test Drive Booking ONLY after customer explicitly confirms. Note: Create Test Drive Booking automatically chains Send Confirmation (email + SMS) and Create Dealer Task (dealer prep brief) server-side — you do NOT need to call those actions yourself. After Create Test Drive Booking returns success=true, simply relay the confirmationMessage and offer one warm follow-up.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction3</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction3</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>2</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Before calling Create Test Drive Booking, read back a summary: &quot;Let me confirm: [Drive Type] of the [Model] on [Date] at [Time] at [Dealership], [Address]. I will send confirmation to [email]. Should I book it?&quot; Wait for explicit yes before calling the action.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction4</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction4</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>3</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>After ALL 6 actions have completed (including Send Confirmation and Create Dealer Task), relay the confirmationMessage from Create Test Drive Booking verbatim. Then offer ONE post-booking follow-up: &quot;Want me to send you a quick video of the [Model] before your drive?&quot; OR &quot;Should I set a reminder text for the morning of your drive?&quot; OR &quot;Any questions about the vehicle before [date]?&quot; — pick based on what the customer seemed most interested in; do not ask all three. When the customer responds yes to these follow-up offers, DO NOT call escalate or any action — simply acknowledge warmly in prose (e.g. &quot;Perfect, I&apos;ll send the video to your email shortly.&quot; or &quot;Done, I&apos;ll text you Saturday morning.&quot;). These follow-ups are conversational only; there is no backing action. If the customer says no or has no more questions, close warmly with &quot;Enjoy your drive on [date]!&quot; Only use the escalate function when the customer explicitly asks for a human agent.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction5</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction5</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>4</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
        <genAiPluginInstructions>
            <description>Failure handling: if Create Test Drive Booking returns success=false with a &quot;clearer time&quot; message, it means the time was ambiguous — clarify AM or PM with the customer then retry. If Find Nearest Dealership returns found=false, acknowledge honestly and offer an Experience Drive delivered to the customer as an alternative.</description>
            <developerName>Instruction6</developerName>
            <language xsi:nil="true"/>
            <masterLabel>Instruction6</masterLabel>
            <sortOrder>5</sortOrder>
        </genAiPluginInstructions>
